cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing lurking behavior in social networks and proposes centrality methods for ranking lurkers. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the development of new methods for analyzing social network data. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper deals with social network behavior and the study of lurking phenomena. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper utilizes network topology to analyze social network data without probing into text contents or user relationships. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing and ranking users in online communities.
